  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[TONE]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we are now end of November, beginning of December 1945.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And although everything is wonderful, there is this great sadness that my brother has not survived, contrary to our expectations, perhaps naive.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But throughout the war in Poland, we took for granted that anybody who has escaped from the German occupation has every chance of being alive and surviving the war.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But that wasn't to be.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] George, similar to my father and myself, felt he wanted to do his bit.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think, in a way, the fact that mother and I were in Poland under the Germans made him focus more on the fight against the Germans, although originally he joined the Royal Air Force and was flying in Burma against the Japanese.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "At the end of '43, he got himself transferred to the Polish Air Force, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] saying that his fight was against the Germans.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's who he wanted to fight.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's where he had something to fight against.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] his objective.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was very brave, because we heard afterwards he was decorated, posthumously, with a cross of valour.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when my parents went to the general command of the Polish Air Force, he told them that George had already seen him before his-- his flight, knowing that he had only one more flight to do of the second round and had volunteered for path-finding duties.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So his chances of survival over the next 10 months until the war ended were probably very, very small.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In any case, that was a great tragedy for both my mother and myself.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
